title: For Sale:  SOLD
postcontent:
For sale is a highly customized Bushmaster Carbon 15. The rifle has been built buy a very competent gunsmith from the ground up as an ultralight, high speed carbine. It has a carbon fiber upper and lower receiver that are both lighter and significantly stronger than the forged aluminum receivers, much similar to the materials and durability of a Glock vs. a 1911. The carbon fiber upper and lower allow the rifle to return to its original form after being crushed or dropped from a building. Likewise, it creates an extremely lightweight design without compromising durability--this is certainly the future of rifles!

The rifle has a low profile gas block installed that can accept a folding iron sight if you desire to use one, while still keeping it out of the way of the optic with the low profile, lightweight design. The barrel is a thin, chrome-lined barrel chambered in .223 or 5.56 with a 1:9 twist that provides great accuracy while still keeping the weight down. Moving down the barrel, there is a custom made and custom threaded free-floating carbon fiber handguard. The free floating design maximizes accuracy, and the carbon fiber material cuts down on weight while still being very strong and heat-resistant. This whole handguard and ring were custom made to this rifle--they cannot be bought or installed without heavy gunsmithing, which of course has already been done for you! 

The optic is a Sightmark Ultra Shot reflex sight with 5 brightness settings and 4 different reticles, including the popular 2 MOA Aimpoint dot and the EOTech ring/dot. The sight has a rock solid, low profile design that will hold a zero under the harshest of environments. 

The trigger is a Jard single stage adjustable trigger that is set to 2 lbs right now. It can either be stiffened or loosened depending on your trigger preferences. The break is crisp and sharp, which allows for very precise single shots. It of course was installed by the same gun smith as well. The lower has a very low shelf that will allow a registered drop in auto sear or lightning link to be installed for some full auto fun!

The buffer tube is a rifle length tube with an Ace Skeleton stock. The rifle length tube reduces both the weight and recoil, and the stock also cuts down on weight while still providing an excellent cheek rest and a length of pull that fits most shooters.

A Hogue pistol grip was installed to replace the stock plastic one. This Hogue grip is rubberized and provides a slip-free grip that is comfortable, looks good, and reduces the already minimal recoil.

Included with the rifle are as follows:

- 1 metal C-Products mag with anti tilt follower
- 1 Bushmaster metal mag with anti tilt follower
- 1 box of M855 green tipped light armor piercing rounds
- Original box and literature from Sightmark reflex
- Neoprene cover for the Sightmark
- Original literature for the rifle and trigger
- Hard case
- Sling and mounting hardware
- 2 picatinny rail risers for an optic
- Rubber recoil pad for stock
- Original trigger, disconnector, hammer, and springs
- Original gas block with sling loop
- Original Bushmaster double heat shield handguard
- Original delta ring assembly

*Please note that both mags come loaded with high quality brass cased PMC! That is 80 rounds of combined PMC and M855 green tipped penetrators.

The price is slightly negotiable, but bear in mind the amount of custom gunsmithing work and parts that have gone into this rifle. I hate to see it go, but I must fund another rifle project that I am working on. NO bill of sale is required. I don't sign them, nor will I make you sign one. You can reach me at (8six5-7sixsix-7fivefivefive). Text is preferred. Please do not email me, as Yahoo has problems with replying to Armslist emails, so I may not be able to reply to you. I am not looking for any trades at this time. Please don't hesitate to shoot me a text if you have any questions or want additional pictures of the rifle. Thanks for looking and God bless!
